#   HEAD tickets

`be head` is the read-only dry-run preview (the POST/GET "what would change" verb). The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [HEAD-003] — `be head` hunk output renders PLAIN on a TTY (commit + `+/-` file rows), should be color like `diff:`/`status`; the `522-619` sub-capture forces `HUNKOutTLV` and the parent likely never re-renders. Producer stays presentation-free; color is bro's job.

 -  [HEAD-004] — `be head be://<parent>` fetches a submodule from its `.gitmodules` URL (github) instead of the SAME parent source first → `WIREUNRCH` abort when offline. `be get` forwards `--source` (GET-011); HEAD's sub recursion doesn't. Order must be parent-source → declared URL.

